# HeadPilot 🚀

### Real-Time Head Controlled Mouse Using OpenCV & Python

HeadPilot is a computer vision project that allows users to control the mouse cursor using head movements detected through a webcam. The system uses OpenCV Haar Cascade classifiers to detect faces and eyes in real time and translates facial movements into mouse cursor actions.

## Features

* Real-time face detection
* Eye detection using Haar Cascade
* Mouse cursor control through head movement
* Hands-free interaction
* Lightweight and easy to run
* Built with Python and OpenCV

## Technologies Used

* Python 3
* OpenCV
* PyAutoGUI
* Haar Cascade Classifiers

## How It Works

1. Captures live video from the webcam.
2. Detects the user's face and eyes.
3. Tracks the face position on the screen.
4. Moves the mouse cursor according to head movements.
5. Updates cursor position in real time.

## Installation

Clone the repository:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/HeadPilot.git
cd HeadPilot
```

Install dependencies:

```bash
pip install opencv-python pyautogui
```

Make sure the following Haar Cascade files are available in the project directory:

* haarcascade_frontalface_alt.xml
* haarcascade_eye.xml

## Usage

Run the script:

```bash
python main.py
```

Press **Q** to quit the application.

## Project Structure

```text
HeadPilot/
│
├── main.py
├── haarcascade_frontalface_alt.xml
├── haarcascade_eye.xml
└── README.md
```

